# type(scope): short summary
#
# Optional body. Use this to explain what and why, not how.
# Try to keep it concise and relevant.
#
# Examples:
#   feat(server): add TLS support to HTTP interface
#   fix(sdk/go): prevent panic in Catalog hydration
#   docs: clarify Swamp registration flow
#
# Footer (e.g., closes #123)

# Allowed types:
#   feat     - a new feature
#   fix      - a bug fix
#   docs     - documentation changes only
#   style    - formatting, missing semi colons, etc.
#   refactor - code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf     - performance improvements
#   test     - adding or fixing tests
#   chore    - changes to the build process or tooling
#   ci       - CI/CD configuration and workflow changes
#   build    - dependency or build system updates

# Suggested scopes:
#   server       - HydrAIDE server (./app/server)
#   core         - core logic or shared modules (./app/core)
#   cli          - HydrAIDE CLI (./app/hydraidectl)
#   sdk/go       - Go SDK (./sdk/go)
#   sdk/python   - Python SDK (./sdk/python)
#   docs         - documentation (./docs)
#   release      - version bump, changelog, or release artifacts

# Scope is optional, but encouraged: (e.g. feat(server): ...)
# Lines starting with '#' are ignored by Git
